Merge pull request #374 from tomaz/master

`NSTableView` binding improvements

Refactored default bond into class.

This allows ditching associated value shenanigans and use pure Swift solution.

Simplified default animations implementation.

It now returns animations in default implementation in `TableViewBond` implementation, so no need for additional setup in `DefaultTableViewBond`.

Added ability to opt in and out of animations on the fly.

To prevent animations set both `insertAnimation` and `deleteAnimation` to nil. Also enabled animations using default builtin bond - doesn’t make sense in having `animated` parameter without it actually animating updates.
Refactored NSTableView configurator to same approach as UITableView uses.

Added configurator protocol for less messy `NSTableView` configuration.

This allows setting up all parameters in the form of protocol conformance which makes table view configuration API simpler.

As side effect this also brings full parameterization support to previously available function. All additional parameters are set to their default values so it’s fully backwards compatible.

I had need of dynamically changing the text color of an UILabel and I find dealing with NSAttributedText to be clumsy. This commit allows the "textColor" attribute of the UILabel to be modified in the same way as the "backgroundColor" attribute of the UIView.

Please go easy on me, this is my first commit on an open source project. I am intentionally making it a small change, I may develop more in the future.
